# Node.js Application with Docker

This project is a simple Node.js application with a PostgreSQL database, containerized using Docker.

## Table of Contents

- [Introduction](#introduction)
- [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
  - [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Docker](#docker)

## Introduction

This project demonstrates a basic setup of a Node.js application with a PostgreSQL database running in separate Docker containers. It includes endpoints for basic CRUD operations on a "schools" table.

## Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following software installed:

- Docker
- Node.js
- npm

## Getting Started

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   git clone https://github.com/Vanshul-Dahiya/rest-api-docker.git
   cd rest-api-docker   

2. Install dependencies:
   npm install 


###  Usage :

To run the Node.js application locally, use the following command:

   npm start

### Docker :

This project includes Docker support for both development and production environments.

To run the application in development using Docker, use:

  docker-compose up

For a production setup, build the Docker image and run the containers:

  docker build -t your-image-name .
  docker-compose up